section.section:
The court:
shall allow a period not exceeding 20 days for the defendant to show cause why the relief sought should not be granted;
after the period, shall inquire immediately into the merits of the case, without other or formal pleadings and without respect to any technical requirement;
may join as parties any persons as is necessary or proper to make a judgment or process effective; and
shall issue a final order that grants appropriate relief.

The Commission shall notify an offender to appear and answer charges on complaint filed by a carrier or on discovery of a violation or infringement by the Commission's own investigation that:
the offender is or has been infringing on or violating a permit granted to the carrier by the Commission;
the offender, without a permit, is exercising or using a right granted in a permit;
a right granted in a permit is being subjected to unrestricted or unregulated competition; or
the offender, without a permit, is serving, wholly or partly, directly or indirectly, a route set forth in a granted permit.
